The paper discusses the development of new rescheduling methodologies that resort to cognitive capabilities, similar to those found in human beings. This involves the integration of reinforcement learning with artificial cognitive capabilities involving perception and reasoning/learning skills embedded in the Soar cognitive architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with scheduling systems, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The use of reinforcement learning also suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the autonomic nature of the scheduling system, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the development of new methodologies, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
